# ── Lead delivery → HubSpot (Breeze AI works the inbounds) ──
# Private App token. HubSpot → Settings → Integrations → Private Apps →
# Create a HubSpot Service Key (or private app) with these CRM scopes:
#   crm.objects.contacts.read    (required)
#   crm.objects.contacts.write   (required — upsert the lead + tag + submission)
#   crm.schemas.contacts.write   (required — auto-creates chainfren_lead_type +
#                                 chainfren_submissions properties)
#   crm.objects.notes.write      (OPTIONAL — adds a timeline note; not offered
#                                 for Service Keys. Skipped automatically if absent.)
# Copy the access token here (and add it in Vercel → Project → Settings → Environment Variables).
# Leave unset locally to no-op the integration (forms still succeed).
HUBSPOT_ACCESS_TOKEN=

# ── Existing integrations (already referenced in the codebase) ──
# SPACE_ID=
# ACCESS_TOKEN=
# OPENWEATHER_API_KEY=
# OPENAI_API_KEY=
